research_municipality_step.notes: Hillsboro, TX operates under a council-manager form of government. The City Council consists of a Mayor and six Council Members, who serve two-year terms. The Mayor and Council seats 1, 3, and 5 are up for election in odd-numbered years, while Council seats 2, 4, and 6 are up for election in even-numbered years. The Mayor presides over the Council and votes only in the event of a tie.
